ncement\", \"from\": 737, \"to\": 753}, {\"ngram\": \"the Paris Games\", \"from\": 757, \"to\": 772}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The timing has sparked fresh accusations from charitable organizations that the government is orchestrating a campaign to clear the capital and its environs of marginalized communities before the global spotlight shines on Paris.\", \"from\": 775, \"to\": 1004, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 998, \"end\": 1003, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999795364, \"rank\": 2.0479142666317816e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The timing\", \"from\": 775, \"to\": 785}, {\"ngram\": \"fresh accusations\", \"from\": 798, \"to\": 815}, {\"ngram\": \"charitable organizations\", \"from\": 821, \"to\": 845}, {\"ngram\": \"the government\", \"from\": 851, \"to\": 865}, {\"ngram\": \"a campaign\", \"from\": 883, \"to\": 893}, {\"ngram\": \"the capital\", \"from\": 903, \"to\": 914}, {\"ngram\": \"its environs\", \"from\": 919, \"to\": 931}, {\"ngram\": \"marginalized communities\", \"from\": 935, \"to\": 959}, {\"ngram\": \"the global spotlight\", \"from\": 967, \"to\": 987}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As the residents of the Vitry-sur-Seine squat gathered their belongings and departed, they were encouraged to board buses bound for other parts ofFrance.\", \"from\": 1006, \"to\": 1159, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the residents\", \"from\": 1009, \"to\": 1022}, {\"ngram\": \"the Vitry-sur-Seine squat\", \"from\": 1026, \"to\": 1051}, {\"ngram\": \"their belongings\", \"from\": 1061, \"to\": 1077}, {\"ngram\": \"buses\", \"from\": 1122, \"to\": 1127}, {\"ngram\": \"other parts\", \"from\": 1138, \"to\": 1149}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, many expressed reluctance to leave the Paris region, where they had secured employment and established lives despite the challenges of finding proper housing.\", \"from\": 1161, \"to\": 1328, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1209, \"end\": 1214, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999795364, \"rank\": 2.0479142666317816e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"reluctance\", \"from\": 1185, \"to\": 1195}, {\"ngram\": \"secured employment\", \"from\": 1238, \"to\": 1256}, {\"ngram\": \"lives\", \"from\": 1273, \"to\": 1278}, {\"ngram\": \"the challenges\", \"from\": 1287, \"to\": 1301}, {\"ngram\": \"proper housing\", \"from\": 1313, \"to\": 1327}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Among those affected were 50 women and 20 children, with at least 10 children enrolled in local schools.\", \"from\": 1330, \"to\": 1434, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"50 women\", \"from\": 1356, \"to\": 1364}, {\"ngram\": \"20 children\", \"from\": 1369, \"to\": 1380}, {\"ngram\": \"at least 10 children\", \"from\": 1387, \"to\": 1407}, {\"ngram\": \"local schools\", \"from\": 1420, \"to\": 1433}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The squat's population had surged following the eviction of hundreds from another squat in \\u00cele-Saint-Denis, near theOlympic Village site, underscoring the interconnectedness of housing insecurity and large-scale events like the Olympics.\", \"from\": 1435, \"to\": 1672, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The squat's population\", \"from\": 1435, \"to\": 1457}, {\"ngram\": \"the eviction\", \"from\": 1479, \"to\": 1491}, {\"ngram\": \"hundreds\", \"from\": 1495, \"to\": 1503}, {\"ngram\": \"another squat\", \"from\": 1509, \"to\": 1522}, {\"ngram\": \"\\u00cele-Saint-Denis\", \"from\": 1526, \"to\": 1541}, {\"ngram\": \"theOlympic Village site\", \"from\": 1548, \"to\": 1571}, {\"ngram\": \"the interconnectedness\", \"from\": 1586, \"to\": 1608}, {\"ngram\": \"housing insecurity\", \"from\": 1612, \"to\": 1630}, {\"ngram\": \"large-scale events\", \"from\": 1635, \"to\": 1653}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 1659, \"to\": 1671}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Paul Alauzy, a spokesperson for M\\u00e9decins du Monde and Revers de la M\\u00e9daille, decried what he termed \\\"social cleansing for the Olympic Games,\\\" highlighting a pattern of evictions targeting vulnerable communities over the past year.\", \"from\": 1674, \"to\": 1904, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Paul Alauzy\", \"from\": 1674, \"to\": 1685}, {\"ngram\": \"a spokesperson\", \"from\": 1687, \"to\": 1701}, {\"ngram\": \"M\\u00e9decins du Monde\", \"from\": 1706, \"to\": 1723}, {\"ngram\": \"Revers de la M\\u00e9daille\", \"from\": 1728, \"to\": 1749}, {\"ngram\": \"social cleansing\", \"from\": 1775, \"to\": 1791}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic Games\", \"from\": 1796, \"to\": 1813}, {\"ngram\": \"a pattern\", \"from\": 1829, \"to\": 1838}, {\"ngram\": \"evictions\", \"from\": 1842, \"to\": 1851}, {\"ngram\": \"vulnerable communities\", \"from\": 1862, \"to\": 1884}, {\"ngram\": \"the past year\", \"from\": 1890, \"to\": 1903}]}, {\"sentence\": \"According to Alauzy, the population of the Vitry-sur-Seine squat had swelled due to the displacement caused by previous clearances, illustrating the collateral damage inflicted by efforts to beautify Paris for the Olympics.\", \"from\": 1906, \"to\": 2129, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2106, \"end\": 2111, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999795364, \"rank\": 2.0479142666317816e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Alauzy\", \"from\": 1919, \"to\": 1925}, {\"ngram\": \"the population\", \"from\": 1927, \"to\": 1941}, {\"ngram\": \"the Vitry-sur-Seine squat\", \"from\": 1945, \"to\": 1970}, {\"ngram\": \"the displacement\", \"from\": 1990, \"to\": 2006}, {\"ngram\": \"